TestNG----unit test framework. Testers can integrate with Selenium and can write test cases.
TDD Framework: Test Driven Development- we can drive our TC's with help of TestNG framework.

Purpose:
--Design Test Cases in systematic way.
--open source, free
--available in form of jar files
--also called java unit testing framework, Junit
Advantages:
--Design Test Cases in systematic way.
--generate good HTML reports
--gives different annotations
--can define priorities/sequence of TC
--dependencies
--grouping
--*************Interview:data provider feature. suppose a login TC is there and we need to use different data for the same TC, 
then we use this data provider.
--
